{
  "analysis": "The background fastText training was still running when the polling loop ended, with the log at 97.3% and ETA ~10s. `/app/work/model_raw.bin` was still 0 bytes because fastText writes the model at completion. We should not interrupt the process; we should verify the training PID is alive, wait briefly for the binary to be written, then evaluate size and accuracy.",
  "plan": "Check whether PID 2581 is still alive. Wait up to 60 seconds in a bounded loop for `/app/work/model_raw.bin` to become non-empty. Then print the final log tail, list/stat model files, and run `fasttext test` on the local test set to verify accuracy.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "pid=$(cat /app/work/train.pid 2>/dev/null || true); if [ -n \"$pid\" ] && [ -d \"/proc/$pid\" ]; then echo \"status=running pid=$pid\"; else echo \"status=finished pid=$pid\"; fi\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "for i in $(seq 1 12); do size=$(stat -c %s /app/work/model_raw.bin 2>/dev/null || echo 0); echo \"wait=$i size=$size\"; if [ \"$size\" -gt 0 ]; then break; fi; sleep 5; done\n",
      "duration": 65.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "tail -20 /app/work/train.log 2>/dev/null || true\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -lh /app/work/model_raw* 2>/dev/null || echo 'No model files'; stat -c 'model_raw.bin size bytes: %s' /app/work/model_raw.bin 2>/dev/null || true\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "/opt/fastText/fasttext test /app/work/model_raw.bin /app/work/test.txt 2>&1 | tail -10 || echo 'test failed'\n",
      "duration": 10.0
    }
  ]
}
